to get content of website¶

In [130]:

Out[130]:
'<HTML><HEAD>\n<TITLE>Access Denied</TITLE>\n</HEAD><BODY>\n<H1>Access Denied</H1>\n \nYou don\'t have permission to access "http&#58;&#47;&#47;www&#46;ambitionbox&#46;com&#47;list&#45;of&#45;companies&#63;" on this server.<P>\nReference&#32;&#35;18&#46;7cb01302&#46;1705253248&#46;87cd06b8\n</BODY>\n</HTML>\n'

cant access the site, so we will one method to get the content¶

In [131]:
# if response code is 403
headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; Win 64 ; x64) Apple WeKit /537.36(KHTML , like Gecko) Chrome/80.0.3987.162 Safari/537.36'}
webpage = requests.get('https://www.ambitionbox.com/list-of-companies?campaign=desktop_nav&page=1',headers=headers).text

Finding our data from page one¶

In [144]:
name=[]
rating=[]
reviews=[]
hq=[]
how_old=[]
no_of_employee=[]

#running for loop and appending in list as above

for i in company:

    name.append(i.find('h2').text.strip())
    rating.append(i.find('span',class_='companyCardWrapper__companyRatingValue').text.strip())
    reviews.append(i.find('span' , class_='companyCardWrapper__ActionCount').text.strip())
    hq.append(i.find('span' , class_='companyCardWrapper__interLinking').text.strip().split('|')[-1])
    how_old.append(i.find('span',class_='companyCardWrapper__interLinking').text.strip().split('|')[-2])
    no_of_employee.append(i.find('span',class_='companyCardWrapper__interLinking').text.strip().split('|')[1])

df=pd.DataFrame({'name':name,
   'rating':rating,
   'reviews':reviews,
   'company_type':ctype,
   'Head_Quarters':hq,
   'Company_Age':how_old,
   'No_of_Employee':no_of_employee,
   })

creating dataframe from 100 pages¶

In [147]:
final=pd.DataFrame()
for j in range(1,100): # loop for 100 pages
    
    url = 'https://www.ambitionbox.com/list-of-companies?campaign=desktop_nav&page={}'.format(j)
    
    headers={'User-Agent':'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 6.3; Win 64 ; x64) Apple WeKit /537.36(KHTML , like Gecko) Chrome/80.0.3987.162 Safari/537.36'}
    
    webpage=requests.get(url,headers=headers).text

    soup=BeautifulSoup(webpage,'lxml') 
    
    company=soup.find_all('div',class_='companyCardWrapper') # the whole container
    
    name=[]
    rating=[]
    reviews=[]
    hq=[]
    how_old=[]
    no_of_employee=[]

    for i in company:

        try: #extracting company name and appending it
            name.append(i.find('h2').text.strip()) 
        except:
            name.append(np.nan) # company name is none if not able to find in container

        try:  #extracting rating and appending it
            rating.append(i.find('span',class_='companyCardWrapper__companyRatingValue').text.strip()) 
        except:
            rating.append(np.nan) # rating is none if not able to find in container
   
        try: #extracting reviews and appending it
            reviews.append(i.find('span' , class_='companyCardWrapper__ActionCount').text.strip())
        except:
            reviews.append(np.nan) #reviews is none if not able to find in container
        
        try: #extracting head quaters name and appending it
            hq.append(i.find('span' , class_='companyCardWrapper__interLinking').text.strip().split('|')[-1])
        except:
            hq.append(np.nan) #headquater is none if not able to find in container
    
        try: #extracting company age and appending it
            how_old.append(i.find('span',class_='companyCardWrapper__interLinking').text.strip().split('|')[-2])
        except:
            how_old.append(np.nan) #company age is none if not able to find in container
    
        try: #extracting no of employee and appending it
            no_of_employee.append(i.find('span',class_='companyCardWrapper__interLinking').text.strip().split('|')[1])
        except:
            no_of_employee.append(np.nan) #no of employee is none if not able to find in container
    

    df=pd.DataFrame({'name':name,
    'rating':rating,
    'reviews':reviews,
    'Head_Quarters':hq,
    'Company_Age':how_old,
    'No_of_Employee':no_of_employee,
    })
  
    final=final.append(df, ignore_index=True)

# Define a function to categorize companies based on the number of employees
def categorize_company(employee_range):
    if 'Lakh' in employee_range:
        return 'Large'
    elif '50k' in employee_range or '1 Lakh' in employee_range:
        return 'Medium'
    else:
        return 'Small'

# Apply the function to create a new 'Company Size' column
df1['company_size'] = df['No_of_Employee'].apply(categorize_company)

# creating bins for company size such as small, medium, large

Data description¶

name column has company name¶

rating is the rating of the company¶

reviews is the review of the company¶

head_quaters is the location of the company head_quaters¶

company_age is the age of the company(how old it is)¶

no_of_employee is the range in which companies have number of employess¶

location is the total number of locations the companies has¶

rating_text is the category of the rating¶

company_size id the size of the company based on the number of the employee it has¶

Average of Company size by rating¶

In [219]:
emp_salary = df1.groupby('company_size')['rating'].mean()

plt.figure(figsize = (10,6))
p = sns.barplot(y = emp_salary.values, x = emp_salary.index, palette = 'cool_r')
plt.title('Average of Company Size by Rating', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
plt.xlabel('Company Size', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Average Rating', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')

for container in p.containers:
    plt.bar_label(container,
                padding = -20,
                fontsize = 17,
                bbox = {'boxstyle': 'square', 'edgecolor': 'red', 'facecolor': 'yellow'},
                label_type="edge",
                fontweight = 'bold'
                 )

# Customize the background color
p.set_facecolor("#f4f4f4")

# Remove the grid lines
p.grid(False)

plt.show()

plt.xlabel('Company Size', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Age of Company', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')

    plt.bar_label(container,
                padding = -20,
                fontsize = 17,
                bbox = {'boxstyle': 'square', 'edgecolor': 'black', 'facecolor': 'yellow'},
                label_type="edge",
                fontweight = 'bold'
                 )

p.grid(False)
